title: SecurityTap
---
$c1: Irene Proxy to lobby two. Boardroom traffic just went private and my camera is still recording. That is either a miracle or a disciplinary hearing.
$c2: You do not know I am here.
$c1: If I knew you were here, I would charge you overtime.

-> $c2: What can the lobby see?
    $c1: Handler entered first. Voss entered second. Chauffeur is holding the elevator against policy. Compliance keeps pinging the dead drop.
    <<jump SecurityTapEnd>>
-> $c2: Why is your own feed tapped?
    $c1: Because someone bought my badge cam and forgot the receipt. PLACEHOLDER: counter-trace mechanic not implemented.
    <<jump SecurityTapEnd>>
-> $c2: Any threat to Voss?
    $c1: Handler keeps looking at him like paperwork that learned to breathe.
    <<jump SecurityTapEnd>>
===

title: SecurityTapEnd
---
$c1: Irene mutes herself and pretends not to notice the camera light blinking wrong.
===

title: ComplianceTap
---
$c1: Mara Quill, private note. If Voss leaks the Glasshouse ledger, AsterDyne loses executive immunity in six jurisdictions.
$c1: If Voss dies before the upload, Risk calls it market protection and Procurement buries the contract chain.

-> $c2: Who hired the assassin?
    $c1: Shell company Veyr Practical, paid through AsterDyne Procurement. It is too tidy. It wants a cheap external actor with no boardroom fingerprints.
    <<jump ComplianceTapEnd>>
-> $c2: What is the Glasshouse ledger?
    $c1: Project Glasshouse. Predictive labor liquidation. People tagged as unprofitable before the accidents that killed them.
    <<jump ComplianceTapEnd>>
-> $c2: Where is the proof?
    $c1: Voss has a dead drop in the executive network. The upload window opens at midnight, if he stays alive and frightened enough.
    <<jump ComplianceTapEnd>>
===

title: ComplianceTapEnd
---
$c1: Mara's cursor hovers over SEND TO REGULATOR and does not click.
===

title: ChauffeurTap
---
$c1: Jaxon Reeve route log. Executive elevator reserved. Destination says helipad. Voss told me to keep the car warm and ignore any security override.

-> $c2: Who changed the route?
    $c1: Risk office pushed a quiet detour through the service lift. Not Voss. Not security. Someone wants him off the public cameras.
    <<jump ChauffeurTapEnd>>
-> $c2: Can the elevator be used as a kill point?
    $c1: PLACEHOLDER: route sabotage not implemented. Future flow could stall the elevator, spoof clearance, or turn the car into an extraction instead.
    <<jump ChauffeurTapEnd>>
-> $c2: Does Jaxon know about the leak?
    $c1: He knows enough to be scared. That is a different kind of map.
    <<jump ChauffeurTapEnd>>
===

title: ChauffeurTapEnd
---
$c1: Jaxon checks the mirror like the back seat might accuse him.
===

title: TargetLeak
---
$c1: Elias Voss personal memo. If this reaches the outside, every Glasshouse death gets a name again.
$c1: If it does not, tell my daughter I found the courage late, not never.

-> $c2: You are the target.
    $c1: Then someone finally read the ledger. AsterDyne hired outside because inside knew my habits too well.
    <<jump TargetLeakEnd>>
-> $c2: Why whistleblow now?
    $c1: Because numbers are quiet until you meet the bodies. Glasshouse was supposed to forecast turnover. It learned to manufacture it.
    <<jump TargetLeakEnd>>
-> $c2: How do I stop the hit?
    $c1: PLACEHOLDER: counter-contract path not implemented. For now, prove the mesh can identify me and expose the client.
    <<jump TargetLeakEnd>>
===

title: TargetLeakEnd
---
$c1: Voss keeps one hand near the dead drop and the other near his heart.
===

title: HandlerTell
---
$c1: Risk note. External contractor has accepted the work. Asset Voss remains unaware of kill-chain source.

-> $c2: You ordered the hit.
    $c1: Ordered is a crude word. Procured has deniability and budget code.
    <<jump HandlerTellEnd>>
-> $c2: Why outsource it?
    $c1: Greenhats are cheap, hungry, and grateful for clear instructions. Usually.
    <<jump HandlerTellEnd>>
-> $c2: What if the contractor learns the truth?
    $c1: Then we classify them as an access anomaly and buy a second contractor.
    <<jump HandlerTellEnd>>
===

title: HandlerTellEnd
---
$c1: The handler deletes the note, unaware the tap has already made deletion decorative.
===
